annotation.TEXT: Okay, I'm low on time, so let's get a move on here.
I'm getting quite a number of ammo pickups here, which is nice.
Aw, man. The star is gonna change the music. Well, that's okay. As long as it changes back to Okkusenman afterwards.
If there's one thing the Bass skins are good at, it's emptying multi-coin blocks!
Screw the pink lemonade! I can hover!
D'oh! Just missed the 6.
However, the fact that it's only a single cannon makes this part easier, which is nice right now since I'm in a hurry here!
Alright, for the next level, I think I'll use Ice Man, since I haven't tried him out yet, and I kind of want to while I have the chance.
Oh, look at this! We've rescued the almighty line piece! Now we can create Tetrises again!
Oh, man. Gotta love that Okkusenman music!
Ah, we've got "The Dance of the Sugar Plum Fairies" music from the NES Tetris (Nintendo version) playing here.
And, just like that, it sends me back to the title screen, with no chance to save my endgame status. Oh, well.
There's a donut, but I think I might've made my situation worse here with that miss. Uh, oh.
Alt. skin votes included 3 for Quick Man (Bass), 1 for Ice Man (Mega Man), 1 for Haggle Man (Ryu), 1 for Peach (Luigi), and 1 for Tetrimino (Sophia III).
Yeah, I'm probably just wasting weapon energy here, but I don't think I'm going to use a Mega Man skin again in this playthrough, so I may as well have some fun with this.
Too bad Ice Man doesn't have an easy way to rapidly hit this multi-coin block, but he can still get 15 the normal way, and he can easily bash his way to the ten coins to the left!
Umm... What's this coin doing here? There's no coin here in the original SMB. Also, it's too high for me to reach. Only the higher jumping (or double jumping or hovering) characters can reach it.
Oh, look at the timer! It's starting at 400 here instead of 300!
Okay, that multi-coin block is in its proper spot, and Ice Man can hit it a lot more safely than Mario can!
Yeah, I couldn't safely get to that donut before it disappeared. Umm... So, how am I gonna get out of this situation?
Aw, I can't freeze Lakitu?
Also, I think I'm gonna homing missile that Birdo, just to be safe.
Yeah, I have no means aside from star power to harm Buzzy Beetles right now.
Ooh, an SMB2 theme. Now, this part always makes me a little nervous, because you never know if a cheepo will shoot out at just the right angle at the wrong time to screw you over.
There we go!
Alright, it's final boss time, against Wart again, with the B-type Tetris music playing now! I may not have any vegetables, but I can feed him a bunch of Crusher bullets and missiles!
I don't know why the credits are jutting forward oddly like that. Maybe it's a glitch in my recording?
That was weird. The kicked shell skipped over the first pit but fell into the second.
Okay, now things are gonna get a bit dangerous over here, because I can't stomp bullets (or eyeballs in this case). I can freeze them with charge shots, but that won't help me for long.
Umm... This pipe back to start is not working. I'm pressing down on it and nothing's happening. Not that you'd want to take that pipe anyway, but it's still technically an inaccuracy.
Oh, yes! It's the Pharaoh Shot again! Let's not lose it this time, and let's remember that it can't fire straight up or down.
What the? This last bullet cannon here should be two bullet cannons stacked on top of each other. That's another inaccuracy.
Alright, now who's next? Well, there was a Haggle Man vote, so sure, why not?
Ooh, this sounds interesting. I'll have to try that out at some point.
Ha! Worked like a charm!
Alright, the first thing I'm going to do here is change those options I altered for the SMW Special World music back to Random.
Umm... I don't know why there was a pause in the music there. Well, let's watch the credits roll, while listening to the SMB3 ending music.
I don't have that much NP, so I'd better aim carefully at the Hammer Bros. here. Or just KO them with the bricks the classic way.
It's a bummer that the Pharaoh Shot doesn't work on Buzzy, though. Also, I summoned my spring by accident there, but I may as well use it.
Aw, the "Hurry up!" warning changed the music, but whatever. This music's awesome too.
Alright, I may as well see if the pipe back to start works.
Ooh, what power up is that?
So, charge shots freeze enemies, eh? Sounds interesting.
Yep, SMW's Special World music does include the original Mario tune here, just like in SMW. (I changed some options to make sure this music played here this time.)
However, before I finish the level, I'm gonna change the music back to Random.
That was kind of close right there. Oh, yeah. I have the energy balancer, so weapon capsules will always fill something up.
Yes! Got the 6 this time!
To be continued...
Huh. I didn't touch the sound options, but for some reason, changing my character's skin also changed the music.
Alright, now the pit before the final boss is once again shorter than usual, probably for the same reason as usual.
Fortunately, no bad luck here.
Ah, the classic graphics and music. Also, my 3-way shot can deal with Buzzies!
Well, that got me the Okkusenman music back, but I wonder why no music was playing at all in this room at first? Did it randomly select a "mute" option or something?
I'm not going to check anymore pipes back to start in this run here. (However, I did check the others off screen later, and the other pipes back to start do function.)
The first of those two pits was also smaller than usual, probably for the same reason that I stated last time.
Oh, yeah. I should try using that Jump Slash ability. It consumes 5 NP per use.
Umm... Where'd the music go? Uh, is this a glitch? Let me try adjusting the options here.
Yeah, but I don't go quite high enough to get up there. That's okay, because I've got another idea.
Votes for Google to change the comment system back: At least 216,433.
I went with the purple Haggle Man last time, so I'll go with the green one this time. (Although, thinking about it now, maybe I should've gone with Shadow from FF6 instead. Oh, well.)
A fat lotta good that weapon energy will be with no subweapons to use it with. And, unfortunately, there are no power ups in 8-1. (But there is a 1-up, and it's in the right spot here.)
Shut up, clock!
Oh, the game explains this power up. It's from the first Ninja Gaiden game.
Now, unlike in 2-1, where the incorrect time limit obviously had to have been a mistake, I'm betting the timer change here was intentional, for the benefit of the slower characters.
Yeah, I can freeze the enemies, but they only stay frozen for a couple seconds. That's not very long at all.
Oh, I'm gonna try something here. I can still use "Rush", right?
Yeah, wreck those bricks!
At least I can stand on the frozen duders, as expected.
Hmm... I'll go with the NES Quick Man first, and I'll switch to the other one if I die.
And, I like that idea, so I'm going with it! However, I'm going to go with the SNES version of the Tetris-mobile this time!
Like that, apparently! I had some good fortune there.

Oh, I guess this is the first time I'm showing this in my videos. Sophia III is always equipped with the "Dive" upgrade in this game (even if you haven't grabbed any power ups yet), and can swim just like in Blaster Master. It's really nice.
Hello, and welcome back to SMB Crossover! The votes are shown above as usual.

Actually, I'm going to change skins for a moment to show what this looks like with the original Sophia III graphics. (Yes, you can change your character's skin on the pause menu during a level. However, I won't normally do this.)
There's an extra small platform there, possibly once again to help the less powerful jumpers cross this pit.
Ooh, what's that? It's a different power up. The game didn't give an explanation for it, but I believe it is the diagonally-downward-shooting fireball from Ninja Gaiden 2... Yep.
Umm... I seriously doubt I'll need infinite lives though.
Screw the lava, for I can ride on the ceiling!
I already know I can't destroy the bullets with this guy, so I'm not even gonna try.
Hey! No jumping over the shell I kicked!

Alright, it is time for the last level of the game! Now, I didn't forget about that vote to use Mario in 8-4. However, someone suggested that I use the Tetrimino (Sophia III) to finish this off with, since I started this whole adventure with the Tetrimino in 1-1.

So, what should I do next? The SMB Special levels? Or the regular SMB levels on Hard difficulty? And, which characters/skins should I use for whatever I do next? Vote now, and we'll find out next time!
Mwahaha! Wreck those bricks!
SML2 music? Oh, come on. We've gotta keep Okkusenman going! (Normally I wouldn't bother with this, but I want that awesome music to keep playing right now.)
Yeah! One last 6 FTW!
And that's game!
Alright, so we're gonna be going with Quick Man for 8-1, because his votes favored 8-1.
Aww, I was hoping the Jump Slash would get me all 15 coins in a quarter of a second (like how you can slay bosses in the first Ninja Gaiden in a fraction of a second with it).
Alright, time to switch back to the Tetris-mobile for the last part!
Yep.
